# Frontend Design

## Typography
- Use Nunito as primary font (rounded sans-serif matching Finch logo energy), system-ui fallback
- Modular scale with `clamp()` for fluid headings; fixed rem for body/UI text
- `text-wrap: balance` on headings to prevent orphans
- `font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums` on data columns
- Minimum 16px body text; use rem/em, never px for body
- Vary weight and size for hierarchy — combine 2-3 dimensions (size + weight + space)

## Color
- Tint all neutrals toward brand hue — never pure gray or pure black (#000)
- 60-30-10 rule: 60% neutrals, 30% secondary, 10% accent (accent works because it's rare)
- Gray text on colored backgrounds looks washed out — use a shade of the background color instead
- Reduce chroma at extreme lightness/darkness to avoid garish tones
- Test contrast: 4.5:1 body text, 3:1 large text/UI components

## Layout & Space
- 4pt spacing base: 4, 8, 12, 16, 24, 32, 48, 64, 96px
- Use `gap` over margins for sibling spacing
- Vary spacing for rhythm — tight groupings + generous separations
- Not everything needs a card container; never nest cards inside cards
- Left-aligned text with asymmetric layouts often feels more designed than centering everything

## Motion
- Duration: 100-150ms feedback, 200-300ms state changes, 300-500ms layout, 500-800ms entrances
- Exit animations at ~75% of entrance duration
- Default easing: `cubic-bezier(0.25, 1, 0.5, 1)` (ease-out-quart)
- Animate only `transform` and `opacity` — everything else triggers layout recalc
- Never `transition: all` — list properties explicitly
- Never use bounce/elastic easing — feels dated; real objects decelerate smoothly
- Stagger cap: total stagger time under 500ms
- `prefers-reduced-motion` is mandatory — provide crossfade alternative or disable

## Anti-Patterns
- No Inter, Roboto, Arial, Open Sans as primary font
- No pure black (#000) or pure white (#fff) — always tint
- No identical card grids repeated endlessly
- No glassmorphism as decoration without purpose
- No gradient text for "impact" on metrics/headings
- No modals unless truly no better alternative
